The number of confirmed COVID-19 cases in West Sussex so far as at 17 December is 127,917 (14,743.2 cases per 100,000 population). In the seven days to 12 December, there were 5,349 new confirmed cases (616.5 new cases per 100,000). In the seven days to 05 December, there were 5,937 new cases, and so the new cases have decreased by 10% (588 fewer cases).
